item.title: Help with put my server online for peeps
item.dc:creator: @eVokki1 Cowie`
item.description:
@eVokki1 wrote:

mod_lol1:

How I dow that?

In your router administration panel ( 192.168.0.1 is usually the I.P To access it, you will be prompted by a login screen, the usual login is something such as admin:password or admin:admin ), you create a service, AKA Let your port through at any time, no logs etc. Then you go to firewall rules and allow that service you just created to be allowed incoming and outgoing traffic at all times.
